    <section id="sect-00003">
    <title>Defining a function</title>
    <para id="para-00006">A function is defined using the <term id="term-00002">def</term> keyword. The first line contains <code class="python inline-code">def</code> followed by the function name (in snake case), parentheses (with any parameters--discussed later), and a colon. The indented body begins with a documentation string describing the function's task and contains the function statements. A function must be defined before the function is called.</para>
