    <section id="sect-00004">
    <title>Benefits of functions</title>
    <para id="para-00011">A function promotes modularity by putting code statements related to a single task in a separate group. The body of a function can be executed repeatedly with multiple function calls, so a function promotes reusability. Modular, reusable code is easier to modify and is shareable among programmers to avoid reinventing the wheel.</para>
