    <note class="practice-program" id="note-00008">
    <title>Terms and conditions prompt</title>
    <para id="para-00018">Write a function terms() that asks the user to accept the terms and conditions, reads in Y/N, and outputs a response. In the main program, read in the number of users and call terms() for each user.</para>
    <para id="para-00019">Given <span class="purple-code">inputs 1 and "Y"</span>, the output is:</para>
    <code class="python" lang="python">
    Do you accept the terms and conditions?
    Y
    Thank you for accepting.
    </code>
    <para id="para-00020">Given <span class="purple-code">inputs 2, "N", and "Y"</span>, the output is:</para>
    <code class="python" lang="python">
    Do you accept the terms and conditions?
    N
    Have a good day.
    Do you accept the terms and conditions?
    Y
    Thank you for accepting.
    </code>
